Package: lpari
Title: Recovery-Calibrated Enumeration for Latent Profile Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Gallardo-Pujol", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "david.gallardo@ub.edu")
  )
Author: David Gallardo-Pujol [aut, cre]
Maintainer: David Gallardo-Pujol <david.gallardo@ub.edu>
Description: Implements LPA-RI, a recovery-calibrated index for choosing the
    number of latent profiles in small-sample latent profile analysis. The
    package includes a lightweight diagonal Gaussian latent profile fitter,
    candidate scoring with calibrated LPA-RI coefficients, a conservative
    null gate, posterior-style plausibility summaries over candidate K values,
    and worked examples using Old Faithful, Reaven-Miller diabetes, iris, and
    Holzinger-Swineford data.
